<exercise id="fs-id1166164827210">
<problem id="fs-id1166164827212">
<para id="fs-id1166164827214">Show that the magnetic field of a thin wire and that of a current loop are zero if you are infinitely far away.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1166168280998">
<para id="fs-id1166168281000">As the radial distance goes to infinity, the magnetic fields of each of these formulae go to zero.</para>
